  "title": "Procurement Manager",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></h2><ul><li>Support procurement function within an organization.</li><li>Executing procurement strategies, managing supplier relationships, and ensuring timely and cost-effective procurement of goods and services.</li><li>Assists in development and implementation of procurement policies, processes, and systems, while adhering to organizational guidelines and industry best practices.</li><li>Vendor selection, negotiation, ensuring favorable terms and conditions.</li><li>Work closely with stakeholders to understand procurement needs and provide efficient procurement support.</li><li>Market research, cost management, and compliance also part of their responsibilities. </li><li>Collaborate across departments and teams to ensure smooth procurement operations and support organizational objectives.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc task assigned by Management or Director.<br /></li></ul><h2><strong>Requirements:</strong></h2><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Supply Chain, Business, Engineering, or related field.</li><li>Minimum 5 years of procurement experience, preferably in ACMV / M&E / Construction.</li><li>Strong knowledge of ACMV materials, equipment, and construction procurement processes.</li><li>Proven experience in vendor sourcing, negotiation, and contract management.</li><li>Good understanding of cost control, market pricing, and compliance requirements.</li><li>Excellent communication, coordination, and stakeholder management skills.</li></ul>",
